description.narrative:
The main objective of the intervention conducted by NGO NDI (National Democratic Institute) is to increase women and youth’s participation in parties and policy making. The specific objectives are:
- Support political parties to initiate internal reforms to make the party more inclusive;
- Assist women and youth wings to influence party policy on key issue areas;
- Support youth and women party wings to collaborate with civil society organizations (CSOs) and national legislators to advance priority issues.
